  "body": "Follow-up on [balance-history improvements](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/9379)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Bad user experience when multiple chains are enabled\r\n  - Add loading screen https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/204568967-bc913690-d694-476b-a3c4-8623c5335b97.png \r\n  - Consider fetching for address and token on all chains first (now we fetch for all accounts and tokens for each chain in order)\r\n  - Batching will speed up\r\n  - More complicated implementation: we could not include the missing chains even if they are enabled but don't have data\r\n- [ ] RPC calls batching when possible (e.g. initial or late update fetch)\r\n- [ ] Improve on fetching for visible tokens by filtering addresses that have balances\r\n  - Move `WalletTokenDto.alwaysVisible` to `status-go` and create an API endpoint `visibleTokens` to use it along `Token.BalancesPerChain`. Notify clients of visible tokens update and cache on demand in NIM\r\n- [ ] Show loading balance \r\n  - Optionally, update waiting for graph state, if the view is opened, as soon as the data is fetched\r\n- [ ] Refactor the preview into a specific data model and separate the balance graph view from the price view\r\n  - See https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/7951#discussion_r1023705959\r\n- [ ] Have a \"moving window\" in the graph to access older history or prune the cache for older balances",
